      <hedline>
        <hl1>Hospital to Build Center To Treat Cancer Patients</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Chief executive Joel Seligman says Northern Westchester Hospital is about to begin construction of $20 million cancer treatment and wellness center in Mount Kisco, NY (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Northern Westchester Hospital in Mount Kisco is about to begin construction of a $20 million cancer treatment and wellness center, part of which is expected to open late next year, said Joel Seligman, the institution's president and chief executive officer.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Northern Westchester Hospital in Mount Kisco is about to begin construction of a $20 million cancer treatment and wellness center, part of which is expected to open late next year, said Joel Seligman, the institution's president and chief executive officer.</p>
        <p>The first floor of the two-story, 34,000-square-foot center will include radiation and chemotherapy treatment sections, as well as the only Gamma Knife Center for noninvasive treatment of brain lesions in the state north of Manhattan. The second floor will house doctors' offices and space for support and wellness programs.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
        <p>IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
